    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains hierarchical categorical data with two dimensions: geographic region (parent category) and country (child category), paired with quantitative emission values (0-10,540.8M metric tons). Synthetic data maintains realistic emission distributions (\u03bc=1,842, \u03c3=2,915) with power-law distribution characteristics typical of environmental data. Regional color coding uses distinct hues meeting WCAG contrast ratios. The packed bubble chart maximizes data-ink ratio by encoding three variables in position (geographic grouping), size (emission magnitude), and color (regional affiliation). Perceptually, saturation progression in color axes follows Stevens' power law for magnitude estimation, while bubble clustering implements Gestalt proximity principles. Statistical validity is maintained through proportional scaling (zMin/zMax bounds) and outlier labeling threshold at >250M tons."
